<div class="parent login-parent">
  <div class="child med-child grn-child">

      <%- include('../partials/messages') %>
      <%# inserting the partial bit of code we defined in partials/messages.ejs %>

      <h1>Warning!</h1>
      <h2>This form will <span class="redSpan">erase the entire Inventory database</span> and replace its contents with the data you upload.</h2>
      <h3>Please contact me (sylvia.moore@netscout.com) for any questions or concerns.</h3>

      <ol>
        <li>Open the new FSL inventory spreadsheet (it will be in .xls format), and save it as .csv format</li>
        <li>Use CTRL+F to make sure there are <span class="redSpan">no double quotes</span> (") anywhere in your .csv file!</li>
        <li>Re-name the column headers of the .csv <span class="redSpan"><em>exactly</em> as shown below</span>: (old name > <span class="bluSpan">new name</span>)</li>
          <p>Item Number > <span class="bluSpan">itemNum</span></p>
          <p>Item Description > <span class="bluSpan">description</span></p>
          <p>Vendor Warehouse > <span class="bluSpan">warehouse</span></p>
          <p>Name > <span class="bluSpan">siteName</span></p>
          <p>Oracle Name > <span class="bluSpan">oracleName</span></p>
          <p>Vendor > <span class="bluSpan">vendor</span></p>
          <p>Vendor Serial > <span class="bluSpan">serial</span></p>
          <p>Onhand Qty > <span class="bluSpan">onhand</span></p>
        <li>Navigate to <a href="https://www.csvjson.com/csv2json">this site</a> and upload your .csv file there</li>
        <li><em><span class="redSpan">Before converting</span></em>, UN-check "parse numbers" and "parse JSON" on the right hand side</li>
        <li>Click Convert and then Download your finished file, which should be called "csvjson.json"</li>
        <li>Open your finished csvjson.json file in Notepad and CTRL+A, CTRL+C to copy the contents</li>
        <li>Paste the copied contents into the box below and click "Upload"</li>
      </ol>



      <form class="" action="/inv/upload" method="post">
        <label for="jsonData">Contents of your csvjson.json file:
          <textarea name="jsonData" rows="20" cols="100"></textarea>
        </label>
        <br>
        <button type="submit" name="button" class="green-butn">Upload</button>
      </form>

</div>
</div>
